Oriana Panozzo https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Oriana_Panozzo 0 Oriana Panozzo (born 1959) is an Australian actress, best known as the second actress to play Susan Palmer in the television soap opera Sons and Daughters as the original actress to play the role, Ann Henderson Stires, was not available when the character was brought back to the show. Other TV appearances include The Young Doctors and Bellamy. Her movie credits include Turkey Shoot. Panozzo has been the principal of a talent school. She has made various short films for many short film festivals. She originally trained at National Institute of Dramatic Art (NIDA).
